amiatp.library/background                   amiatp.library/background

   PURPOSE

   amiatp.library is an AmigaOS AT Protocol (XRPC) client shared library for
   classic Amiga (OS 3.2 / 4.1).  It wraps amihttp.library for HTTPS transport.
   Applications hold opaque handles only; sockets, TLS, JWT buffers, and JSON
   parse trees are never exposed.

   OpenLibrary(AMIATPNAME, AMIATPVERSION) is sufficient.  amihttp.library is
   opened inside InitLib; do not OpenLibrary("amihttp.library") yourself when
   using only amiatp.

   API TIERS

   Tier 0 — AtpBaseTagList / AtpError / AtpGetErrorString
     Per-process defaults (CA path, service URLs, break mask).

   Tier 1 — AtpConnection
     PDS + AppView settings, session JWTs, owns an internal HttpSession.
     Login / refresh / logout.

   Tier 2 — AtpRecord / AtpRecordList
     Generic com.atproto.repo.* get / create / put / delete / list.

   Tier 3 — Bluesky helpers
     Timeline, author feed, profile, createPost, resolveHandle, CDN download,
     and feed-post media getters.

   TYPICAL FLOW

   AtpBase = OpenLibrary(AMIATPNAME, AMIATPVERSION);
   conn = NewAtpConnection();
   SetAtpConnectionAttrs(conn,
       ATPA_CA_BUNDLE, (ULONG)"PROGDIR:cacert.pem",
       ATPA_USERAGENT, (ULONG)"MyApp/1.0",
       TAG_DONE);
   if (AtpLogin(conn, "you.bsky.social", app_password) == 0) {
       struct AtpFeed *feed = NULL;
       if (AtpGetTimeline(conn, 20, NULL, &feed) == 0) {
           /* AtpFeedGetPost / AtpFeedPostGetText ... */
           DisposeAtpFeed(feed);
       }
       AtpLogout(conn);
   }
   DisposeAtpConnection(conn);
   CloseLibrary(AtpBase);

   SetAtpConnectionAttrs() is the varargs form of SetAtpConnectionAttrsA()
   (pragma tagcall).

   OWNERSHIP AND LIFETIME

   - DisposeAtpConnection() frees the connection, JWTs, and HttpSession.
   - DisposeAtpFeed() / DisposeAtpProfile() / DisposeAtpRecord() /
     DisposeAtpRecordList() free those objects.
   - STRPTR returns from getters (DID, handle, post text, image URLs, etc.)
     are library-owned until the parent handle is disposed.  Do not FreeVec()
     them.
   - Disk prefs, app passwords, GUI, and ARexx belong to the application
     (e.g. Seiten).

   DEFAULTS

   ATPA_SERVICE default:  https://bsky.social
   ATPA_APPVIEW default:  https://public.api.bsky.app
   User-Agent default:    amiatp/1.0 (Amiga)

   Authenticated app.bsky.* calls (timeline when logged in) go to the PDS
   service URL; the PDS proxies to AppView.  Hitting public.api.bsky.app
   with a session JWT often returns 401.

   SEE ALSO
	libraries/amiatp.h, SDK/Examples/AtpTest, amihttp.library
amiatp.library/errors                       amiatp.library/errors

   ERROR MODEL

   Most LVOs return LONG: 0 on success, else ERROR_ATP_* (8900+).
   AtpError() returns the last library-wide code.
   AtpConnectionGetLastError() returns the last code for that connection
   (also mirrored to the library last-error on failure).

   AtpGetErrorString(code) returns a static English string for Printf().

   Codes (libraries/amiatp.h):

	8900  ERROR_ATP_NOT_IMPLEMENTED
	8901  ERROR_ATP_OUT_OF_MEMORY
	8902  ERROR_ATP_INVALID_HANDLE
	8903  ERROR_ATP_INVALID_ARG
	8904  ERROR_ATP_NO_HTTP          amihttp not available
	8905  ERROR_ATP_HTTP             transport / Perform failure
	8906  ERROR_ATP_HTTP_STATUS      non-2xx HTTP status
	8907  ERROR_ATP_JSON             Lexicon / JSON parse failure
	8908  ERROR_ATP_AUTH             401 / auth failure
	8909  ERROR_ATP_NOT_LOGGED_IN
	8910  ERROR_ATP_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL
	8911  ERROR_ATP_NOT_FOUND        404
	8912  ERROR_ATP_XRPC             XRPC error object / empty URI

   Wire HTTP status is mapped into these codes inside XRPC helpers; there is
   no separate public GetStatusCode on AtpConnection.
amiatp.library/tags                         amiatp.library/tags

   TIER 0 — AtpBaseTagList (after OpenLibrary)

	ATBT_BREAKMASK          (ULONG) Exec break signal mask for blocking
	                        XRPC (passed through to amihttp).
	ATBT_DEFAULT_USERAGENT  (STRPTR) Default User-Agent string.
	ATBT_CA_BUNDLE_PATH     (STRPTR) Default PEM path for AmiTLS / verify.
	ATBT_DEFAULT_SERVICE    (STRPTR) Default PDS base URL.
	ATBT_DEFAULT_APPVIEW    (STRPTR) Default AppView base URL.

   TIER 1 — SetAtpConnectionAttrsA

	ATPA_SERVICE            (STRPTR) PDS base URL (no trailing slash).
	ATPA_APPVIEW            (STRPTR) AppView base URL.
	ATPA_CA_BUNDLE          (STRPTR) CA PEM path for this connection.
	ATPA_USERAGENT          (STRPTR) User-Agent.
	ATPA_CONNECT_TIMEOUT    (ULONG) Connect timeout seconds.
	ATPA_READ_TIMEOUT       (ULONG) Read timeout seconds.
	ATPA_VERBOSE            (BOOL)  When TRUE, Printf() XRPC URL / status /
	                        JWT length / body previews (CLI debug).

   TIER 2 — SetAtpRecordAttrsA

	ATPR_COLLECTION         (STRPTR) NSIDs e.g. app.bsky.feed.post
	ATPR_RKEY               (STRPTR) Record key (optional for create)
	ATPR_REPO               (STRPTR) DID; default is session DID
	ATPR_JSON_BODY          (STRPTR) Full record JSON escape hatch
	ATPR_TEXT               (STRPTR) Convenience text for simple posts
amiatp.library/AtpBaseTagList               amiatp.library/AtpBaseTagList

   NAME
	AtpBaseTagList -- Set process-wide amiatp defaults.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
	ok = AtpBaseTagList(tags);
	LONG AtpBaseTagList(struct TagItem *tags);

   FUNCTION
	Applies Tier 0 tags to the library base after OpenLibrary().  Strings
	are copied internally.  Pass NULL tags to leave defaults unchanged
	(still returns success).

   INPUTS
	tags - Tag list ending in TAG_DONE, or NULL.

   RESULTS
	Non-zero (TRUE) on success.  0 if the library base is invalid.

   SEE ALSO
	amiatp.library/tags, AtpError()
