amiatp.library/AtpConnectionGetLastError    amiatp.library/AtpConnectionGetLastError

   NAME
	AtpConnectionGetLastError -- Last ERROR_ATP_* for this connection.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
	code = AtpConnectionGetLastError(conn);
	LONG AtpConnectionGetLastError(struct AtpConnection *conn);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the last error recorded on conn (0 if the last operation
	succeeded).  Also updates the library last-error on failure paths.

   RESULTS
	ERROR_ATP_* or 0.  ERROR_ATP_INVALID_HANDLE if conn is NULL/invalid.

   SEE ALSO
	AtpError(), AtpGetErrorString()
amiatp.library/AtpCreatePost                amiatp.library/AtpCreatePost

   NAME
	AtpCreatePost -- Create an app.bsky.feed.post record.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
	err = AtpCreatePost(conn, text, uri_buf, uri_buflen);
	LONG AtpCreatePost(struct AtpConnection *conn, STRPTR text,
	     STRPTR uri_buf, ULONG uri_buflen);

   FUNCTION
	Builds a Lexicon app.bsky.feed.post JSON record with "text" and
	"createdAt", then POSTs com.atproto.repo.createRecord on the PDS.

	createdAt is derived from the HTTP Date: header when available
	(ISO-8601 UTC), so posts are not stamped from a mis-set local DateStamp.

	Requires an active login session.  text length is capped at 300
	characters (Bluesky grapheme limit approximated as bytes).

   INPUTS
	conn       - Logged-in AtpConnection.
	text       - Post body (bytes as provided by the app).
	uri_buf    - Optional buffer for the resulting at:// URI; may be NULL.
	uri_buflen - Size of uri_buf including NUL.

   RESULTS
	0 on success.  Else ERROR_ATP_*.  On success with uri_buf, writes a
	NUL-terminated at:// URI; empty URI after success is ERROR_ATP_XRPC.

   SEE ALSO
	AtpCreateRecord(), AtpLogin()
amiatp.library/AtpCreateRecord              amiatp.library/AtpCreateRecord

   NAME
	AtpCreateRecord -- com.atproto.repo.createRecord.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
	err = AtpCreateRecord(conn, rec);
	LONG AtpCreateRecord(struct AtpConnection *conn, struct AtpRecord *rec);

   FUNCTION
	Creates a repo record from attributes set with SetAtpRecordAttrsA().
	Requires ATPR_COLLECTION and either ATPR_JSON_BODY or ATPR_TEXT.
	On success, updates the record's URI/CID from the response.

   INPUTS
	conn - Logged-in AtpConnection.
	rec  - Configured AtpRecord.

   RESULTS
	0 on success, else ERROR_ATP_*.

   SEE ALSO
	NewAtpRecord(), SetAtpRecordAttrsA(), AtpPutRecord()
amiatp.library/AtpDeleteRecord              amiatp.library/AtpDeleteRecord

   NAME
	AtpDeleteRecord -- com.atproto.repo.deleteRecord.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
	err = AtpDeleteRecord(conn, rec);
	LONG AtpDeleteRecord(struct AtpConnection *conn, struct AtpRecord *rec);

   FUNCTION
	Deletes the record identified by ATPR_COLLECTION + ATPR_RKEY (and
	optional ATPR_REPO).  Requires login.

   RESULTS
	0 on success, else ERROR_ATP_*.

   SEE ALSO
	AtpGetRecord(), AtpCreateRecord()
amiatp.library/AtpDownloadUrl               amiatp.library/AtpDownloadUrl

   NAME
	AtpDownloadUrl -- GET an absolute URL to a DOS file.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
	err = AtpDownloadUrl(conn, url, path);
	LONG AtpDownloadUrl(struct AtpConnection *conn, STRPTR url,
	     STRPTR path);

   FUNCTION
	Performs an HTTP(S) GET of url using the connection's HttpSession
	(same CA bundle / TLS settings as XRPC).  Streams the entity body
	to path (MODE_NEWFILE).  Intended for CDN thumbs/avatars
	(cdn.bsky.app), not for Lexicon XRPC.

	Body size is capped at 512KB.  On failure the file is deleted if it
	was created.

   INPUTS
	conn - AtpConnection (need not be logged in for public CDN URLs).
	url  - Absolute http:// or https:// URL.
	path - Amiga DOS path (e.g. T:Seiten/img1.img).

   RESULTS
	0 on success, else ERROR_ATP_*.

   NOTES
	Does not set Authorization.  For authenticated blob fetch, use
	repo/blob XRPC helpers when added.

   SEE ALSO
	AtpFeedPostGetImageUrl(), AtpFeedPostGetAvatarUrl()
